data.name: CHT Group
data.description: The CHT Group is a specialty chemicals company with a worldwide operating group focused on innovative chemicals as function generators, auxiliaries and additives for industrial processes. Our products optimize production processes in many industries and have an influence on the functionality, appearance and quality of the end-products on the consumer market. The strategy and organization of the CHT Group is focused on a value-oriented and sustainable corporate policy.

data.name: VARIPHOB
data.description: VARIPHOB® provides high performance silicone and wax based water repellents for various applications. Thanks to our many years of experience in the synthesis and emulsification of organically modified silicones and waxes, our products have unique combinations of properties. The VARIPHOB® product portfolio guarantees long-lasting and environmentally friendly protection of mineral surfaces, architectural paints and plasters.

data.name: ULTRALUBE
data.description: ULTRALUBE® Wax additives are essential in printing inks and OPVs to provide surface functionalities like abrasion resistance, anti-blocking and anti-slip.

data.name: SILCO
data.description: SILCO® is leveling, wetting and dispersing additives that are essential in printing inks and OPVs to provide pigment wetting, dispersing and stabilization.

data.name: TUBIBOND
data.description: The TUBIBOND product range offers extensive solutions for the Paper converting industry. TUBIBOND products are highly efficient and utmost sustainable. They are designed to ensure fast and smooth production processes.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8014
data.description: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8014 is a silicone crosspolymer gel used in personal care applications. This high molecular weight specialty silicone elastomer is carried in Dimethicone. It provides a non-tacky, powdery smooth feel and is used in a wide variety of applications for boosting viscosity, esthetics, and soft focus.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ BEAD 8105 EM
data.description: CHT Beausil™ BEAD 8105 EM is an emulsion of a silicone elastomer for personal care formulations. This specialty cosmetic emulsion is designed to deliver spherical elastomeric silicone powder into water-based products and it has a low cyclic content. Key Features  Silky powdery feeling othe n skin Easily used in aqueous and some lipophilic media Matte finish Cold Processing

data.name: CHT Beausil™ FLUID 8301
data.description: CHT Beausil™ FLUID 8301 is a mixture of carrier solvents designed for personal care products. It contains volatile organic ingredients including a non-polar C15 hydrocarbon sustainably sourced from sugarcane. This 100% volatile mixture is used to imitate the feel and volatility of Decamethylcyclopentasiloxane (D5). It creates elegant and light textures with a non-tacky, non-greasy, and silky finish.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ AMO 804
data.description: CHT Beausil™ AMO 804 is a modified siloxane that is used as an ingredient in personal care applications. These amodimethicones are functionalized silicones with nitrogen groups that improve the deposit and the affinity for the hair. It shows excellent combing behavior and provides a good gloss on hair. These silicone polymers are ideal for all kinds of hair care applications where performance is required.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ FLUID 8170 EM
data.description: CHT Beausil™ FLUID 8170 EM is a nonionic silicone emulsion for personal care applications. It is a 60% active non-ionic emulsion of 350 cSt polydimethylsiloxane. This emulsion is produced with an industry-leading small and consistent particle size. This tight particle size distribution ensures easy formulation and outstanding performance. It is designed to be used in a variety of cosmetic applications where a smooth feel and long-lasting shine are desired.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ AMO 8950 EM
data.description: CHT Beausil™ AMO 8950 EM is a cationic emulsion of amodimethicone for use as a conditioning additive in personal care products. These functionalized silicones with nitrogen groups improve the deposit and affinity to the hair. Amodimethicones show excellent combing and provide a good gloss on hair. These silicone polymers are ideal for all kinds of hair care applications where the best performance is required.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8046
data.description: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8046 is a silicone crosspolymer that is used as an ingredient in personal care products. These silicone elastomer gels provide an even matte finish and are an important raw material for modern high-end cosmetic products such as BB creams, lipglosses, pencils, foundations, primers, soft focus, and anti-aging face creams.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8085
data.description: CHT Beausil™ GEL 8085 is a silicone crosspolymer that is used as an ingredient in personal care products. These silicone elastomer gels provide an even matte finish and are an important raw material for modern high-end cosmetic products such as BB creams, lipglosses, pencils, foundations, primers, soft focus, and anti-aging face creams.

data.name: CHT Beausil™ AMO 918
data.description: CHT Beausil™ AMO 918 is a microemulsion of a sugar-modified siloxane. This personal care ingredient is a “sweet” silicone solution for hair. Its unique chemistry of sugar-modified amodimethicone has all the benefits of typical amodimethicones but without weighing the hair down. Using such sugar-modified silicone creates natural softness, best dry and wet combing, and improved shine.

data.name: HANSA
data.seo_description: View all CHT Group HANSA products on Knowde.com. Quickly and easily request a quote, get samples, and download data sheets.

data.name: HANSA ADD 1055
data.description: HANSA ADD 1055 is a high-performing super wetter based on a trisiloxane backbone. It is commonly used as an additive in plant care formulations for industrial agricultural applications to improve wetting, leveling, and distribution. This product can be also used as a spray tank additive to achieve the same effects.

data.name: HANSA AC 2650
data.description: HANSA AC 2650 is an emulsion of a cationic silicone polymer with 37% active content. It is a soil conditioner that is commonly used as a base for formulating soil treatments in agricultural applications. This agrochemical helps to increase water retention in soils and optimize irrigation activity.

data.name: HANSA AC 1085
data.description: HANSA AC 1085 is a high-performing antifoam based on polyether-modified siloxane. This silicone antifoam is used for industrial agriculture formulations such as pesticides, and fertilizers. Alternatively, this product is suitable as a processing additive to control foaming during the production or the filling process.

data.name: HANSA RELEASE F 1156
data.description: HANSA RELEASE F 1156 is a 60% solids, concentrated version of CHT’s premiere EM-350-35 FGK emulsion. It provides a clean release with less sticking and adds shine and surface finish. This product is used for food release, bakery release, conveyor belts, and lubrication applications.
